If they make their dots stack then ya I agree with you, but in their current state you pretty mnuch have to divide that damage by the number of necros there which is usually more then 1, so you get a much decreased DPS<br>
<br>
Now on the druid/mage/wiz issue<br>
I see it slightly different then the way you described it earlier, but not a whole lot<br>
I always go back to the way it used to be pre 50 pretty much<br>
<br>
I see that in the short burn wizards should always be a LOT ahead of both druids and mages.  Thats what they specialize in, casuing a LOT of damage, VERY fast, a wizard in full burn should be dealing out WAY more damage then your uber rogue or whatever<br>
Mage should be second in full burn, and very much more powerful in druids in this respect, druids are a priest class, they are not designed to deal quick damage in full burn, and this is seen by the recast delay on many of their nukes<br>
<br>
However, in the long burn wizards should still outrun mages, by a fairly large number, BUT druids/mages should have about equal DPS in pure nukes in the long term<br>
<br>
So on a raid it would look like this<br>
Short Burn<br>
Wizard: insane damage I dont really know what to compare it to<br>
Mage: pretty good damage, significantly better then a rogue<br>
Druid: a bit better then a rogue<br>
<br>
Long Burn<br>
Wizard: about the same as a rogue<br>
Mage: about the same as a monk<br>
Druid about the same as a monk<br>
<br>
Long burn /w pet<br>
Mage should outdamage a rogue, this is gonna sound like I am just favoring a mage but in the long burn where a pet is allowed and properly positioned we should outdamage a rogue, if we burn our full mana bar, which wont happen because we are needed for mods anyways<br>
My point is that mages can not use pets on all encounters, so if you average out DPS with a pet and without a pet, we end up overall for all the raids about the same as a wizard, this would make mages a more situational caster then wizards, so they have the edge there, and this comparison does not include bane spells where obviously the wizard goes far ahead of the rest<br>
<br>
On druid balance I think a druid should be healing better then they currently are they are a priest class and should achieve their balance through healing upgrades, not nuking ones<br>
Clerics will always have the edge in CH and such, but druids should be able to take care of a group of casters fine, they already do a decent job, but their increase through balancing should be through healing not nuking<br>
<br>
