<br>
We casters derive the vast majority of our power from within ourselves, in particular our spell book.  Melees require weapons and armor to act effectively.  A naked caster is more powerful than a naked melee.  The balance is that gear improves melees more than it improves casters.<br>
<br>
If casters were as improved by gear as melees are, then we would simply dominate them.  A good weapon can easily double the sustained damage output of a melee compared to a more common weapon.  If I could hold a wand that doubled <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>my</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> damage output, then people would abandon rogues and monks in droves, and all we would need are mages and druids, and a smattering of other classes.<br>
